title: American Avoids Extradition to Egypt After Release From Dubai Detention
description: Sherif Osman, an Egyptian-American dual national, is back in the U.S. after facing possible extradition to Egypt over criticizing the government.

title: From Obama to Neymar, Tributes to Pelé Pour In
description: World leaders and some of the biggest names in soccer paid tribute to Pelé, who rose from poverty to become a global ambassador for what he called “the beautiful game.”

title: Beijing Calls for Measured, 'Science-Based' Response to Its Covid Outbreak
description: Chinese reactions to new screening protocols by the U.S. and other countries varied, with some condemning what they see as discriminatory and unscientific measures against China, while others expressed acceptance.

title: Canada Shifts on China To Build Credibility With Allies
description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau’s administration has shifted from efforts to strengthen ties with China to publicly criticizing its behavior as disruptive.

title: Brazilian President-elect Says He Will End Illegal Amazon Deforestation
description: Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva will face challenges, however, including those rooted in his commitments to expand social spending.

title: The Bravery and the Recklessness of Ukraine's Improvised Army
description: Helping repel the Russian invasion are army units with limited military experience. The question for their country is whether they can stay alive long enough to succeed.

title: Netanyahu Sworn In for Sixth Term as Israeli Prime Minister
description: Benjamin Netanyahu was propelled back to the premiership by a coalition of ultranationalist and religious parties that will wield unprecedented power.

title: Middlemen Snag Carbon-Credit Cash Aimed at Peruvian Amazon
description: Only a small amount of money designated for rainforest preservation reaches the people who live there.

title: Russian Politician and Businessman Dies After Falling From Hotel Roof
description: The demise of a lawmaker who owned a sausage-making company follows the deaths of several other high-profile Russians in violent or mysterious circumstances in recent months.

title: Russia Launches Fresh Missile Barrage at Targets Across Ukraine
description: Ukraine’s armed forces said 69 missiles were fired by Russia, and 54 of them were downed by Ukrainian air defenses.

title: South Korea Takes Hard Look at Strategy After North's Drone Flights
description: South Korean President Yoon Suk-yeol berated his defense minister over the military’s failed response to the airspace invasions by Pyongyang.

title: Europe Taps Tech's Power-Hungry Data Centers to Heat Homes
description: With an energy crisis hitting Europe, governments are exploring ways to recycle electricity used on social-media scrolling, conference calls and video streaming to help heat homes and offices.
